egames/uploads/cropped-TEI-Workshop-Website-Logo.png\" /></a>\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\r\n\t  \t\t\t\t<div id=\"menu-toggle\">\r\n\t  \t\t\t\t\t<i class=\"fa fa-bars\"></i>\r\n   \t\t\t\t\t</div>\r\n\r\n\t  \t\t\t\t<nav id=\"site-navigation-mobile\" class=\"main-navigation\" role=\"navigation\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"menu\"><ul>\n<li ><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/\">Home</a></li><li class=\"page_item page-item-21\"><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?page_id=21\">Original Studio Proposal</a></li>\n<li class=\"page_item page-item-36\"><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?page_id=36\">Studio Organizers</a></li>\n<li class=\"page_item page-item-95 current_page_item\"><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?page_id=95\" aria-current=\"page\">Workshop Results</a></li>\n</ul></div>\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</nav><!-- #site-navigation-mobile -->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<h2 class=\"description\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\tTEI 2015 Studio\t\t\t\t</h2>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\r\n\t  \t</div>\r\n\r\n\t</header><!-- #masthead -->\r\n\r\n\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"site-content\">\r\n\t<div id=\"primary\" class=\"content-area\">\r\n\t\t<main id=\"main\" class=\"site-main\" role=\"main\">\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n<article id=\"post-95\" class=\"post-95 page type-page status-publish hentry\">\r\n\t\r\n\t\r\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\"> \r\n\t     <h1 class=\"entry-title\">Workshop Results</h1> \r\n\t</header><!-- .entry-header --> \r\n\r\n\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\t\t\r\n\t\t<p>Thank you to all the wonderful participants who came and played with us at Stanford in February 2015! \u00a0We had a great time and were totally blown away by the creativity and energy everyone brought to the workshop.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15673069884_b4b8324d2a_z.jpg\"><img class=\"  wp-image-98 alignnone\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15673069884_b4b8324d2a_z-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Masks\" width=\"402\" height=\"208\" /></a>\u00a0<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293692221_69e3d7c65c_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-99\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293692221_69e3d7c65c_z-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Brainstorm Dancing\" width=\"407\" height=\"224\" /></a></p>\n<p>We focused on low-tech protoyping during the workshop, emphasizing the design of playful interactions over technical achievement. \u00a0The tech platform we provided were Makey Makey boards, a simple system for connecting physical circuit building with digital input. \u00a0By default, a Makey Makey can output up, down, left, right, space and click commands, which is enough for many simple web games. \u00a0Some participants also created their own basic software as well, using the\u00a0visual programming\u00a0environment\u00a0Scratch.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16108111130_5bd24467f7_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-100\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16108111130_5bd24467f7_z-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Scratch\" width=\"394\" height=\"227\" />\u00a0<img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-101\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15675589013_f9de2ce75c_z-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Makey Makey\" width=\"391\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15675589013_f9de2ce75c_z-300x201.jpg 300w, https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15675589013_f9de2ce75c_z.jpg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 391px) 100vw, 391px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Most of the design work went into thinking about to create circuits on and across the bodies and clothing of the game players, using alligator clips and conductive fabric. \u00a0Teams of participants created playful versions of Simon Says and Tetris, adaptations of hand-jive and color matching games, and some original dancing &amp; head-butt-based interactions.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16269494706_f4feb8583c_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-103\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15673067524_abf62fcda6_z-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Head Butt\" width=\"390\" height=\"219\" /></a> <a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109300479_f6f9d8bf66_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-106\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109300479_f6f9d8bf66_z-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Simon Says\" width=\"395\" height=\"258\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109252367_40571a8452_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-104\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109252367_40571a8452_z-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"Color Matching\" width=\"423\" height=\"222\" /></a>\u00a0<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293641091_f0890786f7_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-108\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293641091_f0890786f7_z-300x201.jpg\" alt=\"Tetris\" width=\"391\" height=\"258\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293319001_8a66a02bf3_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-102\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16293319001_8a66a02bf3_z-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"Hand Jive\" width=\"404\" height=\"224\" /></a>\u00a0<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15672697234_e3689ef9fb_z.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-105\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/15672697234_e3689ef9fb_z-300x188.jpg\" alt=\"Animal Dancing\" width=\"407\" height=\"256\" /></a></p>\n<p>Check out the Flickr album for more photos and videos of each of the prototypes:\u00a0<a title=\"Flickr Album\" href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/jtanenbaum/sets/72157649916970748/\">https://www.flickr.com/photos/jtanenbaum/sets/72157649916970748/</a></p>\n<p>We also produced a quick &amp; dirty poster following the workshop:\u00a0<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/TEI-Studio-Poster.pdf\">TEI Studio Poster</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109557647_d6ca7a6298_k.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone  wp-image-109\" src=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu//wp-content/wearablegames/uploads/16109557647_d6ca7a6298_k-1024x684.jpg\" alt=\"Group\" width=\"721\" height=\"529\" /></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\t\t\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\r\n</article><!-- #post-## -->\r\n\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\r\n\t\t</main><!-- #main -->\r\n\t</div><!-- #primary -->\r\n\r\n\r\n\t<div class=\"sidebar\">\r\n\t\t<div id=\"secondary\" role=\"complementary\">\r\n\t\t\t<div class=\"widget-area\">\r\n\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t\t<aside id=\"search-2\" class=\"widget widget_search\"><form role=\"search\" method=\"get\" class=\"search-form\" action=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/\">\r\n\t<label>\r\n\t\t<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Search for:</span>\r\n\t\t<input type=\"search\" class=\"search-field\" placeholder=\"Search &hellip;\" value=\"\" name=\"s\">\r\n\t</label>\r\n\t<input type=\"submit\" class=\"search-submit\" value=\"Search\">\r\n</form>\r\n</aside>\t\t<aside id=\"recent-posts-2\" class=\"widget widget_recent_entries\">\t\t<h1 class=\"widget-title\">Recent Posts</h1>\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?p=34\">Studio Organizers</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<li>\n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?p=1\">Costumes and Wearables as Game Controllers Studio at TEI 2015</a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t</aside><aside id=\"archives-2\" class=\"widget widget_archive\"><h1 class=\"widget-title\">Archives</h1>\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li><a href='https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?m=201410'>October 2014</a></li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</aside><aside id=\"categories-2\" class=\"widget widget_categories\"><h1 class=\"widget-title\">Categories</h1>\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li class=\"cat-item cat-item-1\"><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?cat=1\">Uncategorized</a>\n</li>\n\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</aside><aside id=\"meta-2\" class=\"widget widget_meta\"><h1 class=\"widget-title\">Meta</h1>\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<li><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/wp-login.php\">Log in</a></li>\n\t\t\t<li><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?feed=rss2\">Entries <abbr title=\"Really Simple Syndication\">RSS</abbr></a></li>\n\t\t\t<li><a href=\"https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/?feed=comments-rss2\">Comments <abbr title=\"Really Simple Syndication\">RSS</abbr></a></li>\n\t\t\t<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/\" title=\"Powered by WordPress, state-of-the-art semantic personal publishing platform.\">WordPress.org</a></li>\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</aside>\t\t\t\t\r\n\t\t\t</div>\r\n\t\t</div><!-- #secondary -->\r\n\t</div><!-- .sidebar -->\r\n\t\r\n\t</div><!-- #content -->\r\n\r\n\t<footer id=\"colophon\" class=\"site-footer\" role=\"contentinfo\">\r\n\t\t<div class=\"site-info\">\r\n\t\t\tGravit Theme powered by WordPress\t\t</div><!-- .site-info -->\r\n\t</footer><!-- #colophon -->\r\n</div><!-- #page -->\r\n\r\n<script type='text/javascript' src='https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/wearablegames/themes/gravit/js/navigation.js?ver=20120206'></script>\n<script type='text/javascript' src='https://wearablegames.ics.uci.edu/wp-content/wearablegames/themes/gravit/js/skip-link-focus-fix.js?ver=20130115'></script>\n<script type='text/javascript' src='https://wearablegames.